name: Su-27 fighter aircraft
fulldate: On October 10, Povitryany Forces lost a Su-27 from the 39th BrTA,piloted by Colonel Oleg Shupik. Shupyk, already a middle-aged pilot born in|1966, graduated from the Chernihiv Higher Military Aviation School in 1987,rose to the rank of deputy chief navigator and inspector of the navigation|service of the Center Air Command. In 2006, he retired from the Povitryany Forces and worked in the Ministry of Transport and various aviation|structures of Ukraine. With the beginning of the war,the 39th BrTA returned to service for a position in the navigation service of the brigade. It is known|that he died on October 10 near the village of Shishaki, Poltava region, and there are no Russian requests for the destruction of Ukrainian Su-27s on that|day, as well as other types of aircraft.|The funeral of another veteran of the 39th BrTA, Colonel Oleg Shupik, who died in a sortie on October 10, 2022.As|usual, there is no application for the downing of this Su-27 from the RF Ministry of Defense.

name: Su-25 close air support aircraft
fulldate: Every day at 9 a.m. during the Russian-Ukrainian war,|Ukrainians observe a minute of silence in memory of their|fallen compatriots. On April 29, let's remember the 28-year-|old captain of the 299th tactical aviation brigade named|after Lieutenant General Vasyl Nikiforov, the attack pilot|Oleksandr Korpan.|The story of Captain Oleksandr Korpan was told by Army Inform|journalists.|Oleksandr Korpan was born in Sevastopol. While studying at|the Kharkiv National University of the Air Force of Ukraine|Photo:armyinform.com.ua|named after lvan Kozhedub, he obtained the specialty of an|attack pilot and mastered the Su-25 aircraft. After graduation, he was sent to serve in the 299th Tactical Aviation Brigade named after|Lieutenant General Vasyl Nikiforov.|Oleksandr was repeatedly involved in the Operation of the United Forces in the east of Ukraine. With his professionalism and|diligence, he won the title of the best fighter pilot. In 2021, he was awarded departmental honors: the "Mastery, Honor, Courage"|commemorative badge,the "For Achievements in Military Service" honorary badge, and the "10 Years of Faithful Service" medal.|On March 2,Oleksandr Korpan was returning from another combat mission.His plane was suddenly hit by enemy fire.The car caught|fire.|"Captain Korpan performed a real feat by taking the plane engulfed in flames away from the airfield and at the cost of his own life|saved the lives of his brothers and many civilian residents of the city of Starokostyantyniv, where this tragedy occurred,"eyewitnesses|reported.|The stormtrooper pilot was buried in the town of Pidhaytsi, near Ternopil. In addition to his brothers, even strangers came to see him|on his last journey.|"We didn't know him personally, but we came to thank the guy for protecting our homes.Now he will protect us from the sky…"- said|the grateful townspeople.
